- Usability
  - Include timestamp-less entries always regardless of the MinTimestamp setting
  - Use the file modification time as the fallback timestamp if no timestamp is present in the line
  - Dry-run mode (list matched files without merging)
  - Including / excluding symlinks during directory traversal

- Output formatting
  - Add unified log level support to format output logs in IDE better (print log level just like timestamp)
  - Opt in to add standardized log level to the output
  - Opt in to remove timestamp from raw line
  - Opt in to remove log level from raw line
  - Custom source name format template (beyond simple --alias pat=name)
  - Custom timestamp output format
  - Default local timezone if no timezone information in the timestamp
  - Allow breaking strict line ordering in favor of keeping logs from same source together, up to a configurable threshold (e.g. 1 second)

- Code quality
  - Aggressively simplify the code so we can easily implement advanced algorithms and features in the future
  - Complete unit tests (notably: no tests for core merge logic in file_merge.go)

- Performance
  - Read files concurrently during merge (prefetch exists, but the merge loop itself is sequential)
  - Experiment with splitting files into chunks and processing in parallel (stub code exists but is unused)
  - Take max open file descriptor limit into account; fall back to intermediate merge files when too many inputs
